# KIT · [Node-ref] — .gitignore that ENFORCES the kit's conventions (not just hygiene).
# Every group below is load-bearing: it explains WHY that line must stay ignored.

# --- Dependencies & build output (noise, not source; regenerable) ---
node_modules/
.pnpm-store/
dist/
out/
.astro/
.next/
.turbo/
*.tsbuildinfo

# --- Env: environment secrets NEVER go into the repo ---
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# --- Claude Code (LOAD-BEARING) ---
# NB: the kit deliberately COMMITS .claude/settings.json + skills/ + commands/ (harness assets
# shared with the team) and ignores ONLY the local parts below. If instead in YOUR repo you
# gitignore all of .claude/, add the exceptions or the assets won't be shared:
#   !.claude/settings.json
#   !.claude/skills/
#   !.claude/commands/
# settings.local.json is the PERSONAL per-machine allow-list: it's gitignored on purpose
# (it grows, contains literal paths/env of your machine, must not be shared nor committed).
.claude/settings.local.json
# Dated backups from periodic pruning of the allow-list: same reason, never in the repo.
.claude/settings.local.json.bak.*
# Scheduled tasks lock: local runtime state of the harness, not shareable.
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
# Ephemeral worktrees created by agents: work artifacts, not source.
.claude/worktrees/

# --- Encrypted secrets (LOAD-BEARING) ---
# Private encryption keys (e.g. age) NEVER go into the repo: kept outside (password manager + offline backup).
# *.age is ignored with ONE exception: the test-only committed fixture, needed for the encrypt/decrypt round-trip tests.
*.age
!scripts/tests/fixtures/age/dev-test.age
# Temporary DECRYPTED output: the plaintext product of a decrypt is never committed.
secrets/*.dec.yaml
secrets/*.plain.yaml

# --- OS / Editor ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp

# --- Logs ---
*.log
logs/
